This bacon is filled with flavor and has been slowly smoked with natural hardwoods, so you may find it irresistible. Who Makes Wright Brand Applewood Smoked Thick Cut Bacon? This Applewood bacon comes from Tyson Foods, Inc., which is an American multinational food company. As of today, Tyson Foods is one of the largest processors of chicken, beef and pork in the entire country. The company is also committed to creating the best food. What Can I Do With This Smoked Bacon? While you eat them after they're cooked, you can also use this Applewood bacon to create delicious cuisines. For example, placing strips of bacon in your sandwiches, burgers, lasagna and salad can heighten their flavor immensely. And if you crumble your smoked bacon into tiny bits, they become a tasty topping for pizza, French fries, spaghetti and more. With thick, high-quality bacon like this, you can get creative. Great Meal for Busy Parents When you're short on time but want to prepare a warm, yummy meal, this smoked bacon comes in handy. All you have to do is place the strips on a hot stove and flip them over. Within minutes, you'll have big pieces of crispy bacon just waiting for you. Large Quantity Makes Sharing Easy Since this particular option contains four pounds of smoked bacon, you can cook enough for the entire family. Whether you're hosting a barbecue or simply want to prepare a hearty dinner, this should be more than sufficient. Easy To Store This Applewood bacon comes in a resealable package, which is easy to stack into a freezer. Since it's resealable, getting your desired amount of bacon is nearly effortless and produces little mess.

descriptors.name: Del Duca Prosciutto (14 oz.)
descriptors.longDescription: Prosciutto is a favorite Italian treat of pork dry-cured with sea-salt. By using all-natural ingredients, Del Duca Prosciutto delivers an authentic taste that works well in a variety of dishes. This large package can be used to add a layer of flavor to your everyday dishes or can be served at a party where everyone will enjoy the savory, sweet taste. What Are Some Recipes for Daniele Gourmet Selection Prosciutto? There are many ways to use Del Duca Prosciutto. It is good to eat by itself. However, there are other ways to enjoy meat. You can wrap cheese with it or enjoy it on artisan bread. You can chop it up and add it to pasta dishes or combine it with peas. Some of the best prosciutto recipes include wrapping asparagus or adding it to pizza. Use prosciutto as a bacon substitute in your eggs Benedict. Prosciutto with fruit, vegetables and olives is also a delicious treat. What Is the Best Way to Serve Boneless Prosciutto? Prosciutto needs to be refrigerated until ready to consume. However, it tastes best at room temperature. When ready to serve, remove the container from the fridge and allow it to come to room temperature, about 10 to 20 minutes. Refrigerate any remaining servings. Is Daniele Del Duca Prosciutto Gluten-free? Daniele Prosciutto does not contain gluten and is free of added MSG. This prosciutto package is made with all-natural ingredients with only two ingredients: pork and salt. It is free of allergens such as soy, dairy or eggs. The prosciutto is never heat-treated. There are no chemicals or preservatives added to keep the prosciutto fresh. Daniele Prosciutto is made in the United States. What is the Serving size of Del Duca Boneless Prosciutto? Each 14 oz. container of Del Duca Boneless Prosciutto by Daniele has 14, 1 oz servings. Each serving has 50 calories with just 3 grams of fat and 8 grams of protein.
